Sidedness –intraindividual differences between the left and the right carotid bodies
Laterality –intraindividual differences that occur in either side but are consistently present
between the carotid bodies

Conclusion
Transcriptomic data indicate the existence of
intra-individual lateral differences between the carotid
bodies.
These differences are not linked to a specific side of the
body suggesting CB laterality but not sidedness.
